R Notebook: Function

f1 <- function(x){
  result <- x^2-5
  return (result)
}

f2 <- function(x){
  result <- sqrt(x)
  return (result)
}
print(f1(2))
## [1] -1
print(f2(3))
## [1] 1.732051

#h(m, n) = (√m/n) + m − 2n
h <- function(m, n) {
  hx <- (sqrt(m)/n) + m - 2*n
  return(hx)
}
h
## function(m, n) {
##   hx <- (sqrt(m)/n) + m - 2*n
##   return(hx)
## }
h(0,1)

a

#f(a, b) = (a + b)ab
f <- function(a, b) {
  fab <- (a+b)%*%a%*%b
  return(fab)
}
f(a,b)
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]  458  532
## [2,]  706  820

#MATRIX
m <- matrix(c(3:6),2,2,TRUE)
n <- matrix(c(2:5),2,2,TRUE)
m
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]    3    4
## [2,]    5    6
n
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]    2    3
## [2,]    4    5
#h(m, n) = |m|n − mn
h <- function(m,n){
  mn <- det(m)*n - m%*%n
  return(mn)
}
h(m,n)
##      [,1] [,2]
## [1,]  -26  -35
## [2,]  -42  -55

g <- function(x) {
  gx <- t(x)-2*x
  return(gx)
}
g(x)

## [1,]   -4   -4

Constant function

Reference for plot types can be accessed here http://www.sthda.com/english/wiki/generic-plot-types-in-r-software

f <- function(x){
  #suppose c = 2
  fx <- 2
  return (fx)
}

input <- 1:10
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "l", xlab = "x", ylab = "y")

Linear Function

f <- function(x){
  #a=1 and b=2
  fx <- 1*x+2
  return(fx)
}

input <- -1:10
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "l", xlab = "x", ylab = "f(x)")

## Quadratic Function

f <- function(x){
  #a<0
  fx <- -1*x^2+2*x+1
  return(fx)
}

input <- -20:22
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "l", xlab = "x", ylab = "f(x)")

## Polynomial Function

f <- function(x){
  fx <- x^3-3*x^2+x-1
  return(fx)
}

input <- seq(-10, 11, 0.1)
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "l", xlab = "x", ylab = "f(x)")

## Rational Function

f <- function(x){
  fx <- 1/x
  return(fx)
}

input <- seq(-10, 10, 0.1)
#to remove 0 from the domain of f
input <- input[-which(input==0)]
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "p", xlab = "x", ylab = "y")

Exercise 4

#f(x) = sin(x)
f <- function(x) {
  fx <- sin(x*pi/180)
  return(fx)
}

input <- seq(-180,180,0.1)
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "l" , xlab = "x" , ylab = " plot f(x)" )

f <- function(x){
  fx <- log10(x)
  return (fx)
}

input <- 0:100
plot(input, sapply(input, f), type = "p", xlab = "x", ylab = "f(x)")
